I catch a taxi to work five days a week. The strict lockdown rules Transport Minister Fikile Mbalula imposed on the public transport system mean I’m at work hours before the copy streams in and must leave before the sun is down – whether my work is done or not. But I’m not complaining, not after I heard my taxi driver’s tale of woe. “It’s bad, man,” he says with a sad face. “It is very difficult to cope or even live during this lockdown. “I need to be paid so that I can feed my family. Right now, I...